{{Infobox language family |name=Arawán |altname=Arauán |region=[[Brazil]] and [[Peru]] |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Macro-Arawakan languages|Macro-Arawakan]] ? |map= Arawan languages.png |mapcaption= |iso5=auf |glotto=araw1282 |glottorefname=Arawan }}
'''Arawan''' (also '''Arahuan''', '''Arauan''', '''Arawán''', '''Arawa''', '''Arauán''') is a family of languages spoken in western [[Brazil]] ([[Amazonas State, Brazil|Amazonas]], [[Acre (state)|Acre]]) and [[Peru]] ([[Ucayali Region|Ucayali]]).
==Family division==
Arauan consists of half a dozen languages:
* [[Arawá language|Arawá]] † * [[Kulina language|Kulina]] * [[Deni language|Deni]] * [[Jamamadí language|Jamamadi]] * [[Paumarí language|Paumari]] * [[Zuruahá language|Suruwahá]]
