{{Infobox language |name=Khinalug |nativename=каьтш мицI / kätš micʼ |pronunciation={{IPA|[kætʃ mit͡sʼ]}} |states=[[Azerbaijan]] |region=[[Quba Rayon|Quba]] |speakers=1,000 |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Caucasian |fam1=[[Northeast Caucasian languages|Northeast Caucasian]] |script= [[Cyrillic script]], [[Latin script]] |iso3=kjj |glotto=khin1240 |glottorefname=Khinalugh |map=Northeast Caucasian languages.png |mapcaption={{legend|#FF3300|Khinalug}}(in Azerbaijan) |notice=IPA }}
'''Khinalug''' (also spelled '''Khinalig''', '''Khinalugi, Xinalug(h), Xinaliq''' or '''Khinalugh''') is a [[Northeast Caucasian languages|Northeast Caucasian]] language spoken by about 1,500 people in the villages of [[Khinalug]] and Gülüstan, [[Quba]] in the mountains of [[Quba Rayon]], northern [[Azerbaijan]]. It forms its own independent branch within the Northeast Caucasian language family.<ref name="EthNCfam">[http://www.ethnologue.com/show_family.asp?subid=215-16 Family tree of Northeast Caucasian languages at Ethnologue]</ref>
Khinalug is [[endangered language|endangered]],<ref>[http://www.helsinki.fi/~tasalmin/chris.html Published in: Encyclopedia of the world’s endangered languages. Edited by Christopher Moseley. London & New York: Routledge, 2007. 211–280.]</ref> and classified as "severely endangered" by [[UNESCO]]'s [[Atlas of the World's Languages in Danger]].<ref>[http://www.unesco.org/culture/ich/index.php?pg=00206 UNESCO Interactive Atlas of the World’s Languages in Danger] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090222090430/http://www.unesco.org/culture/ich/index.php?pg=00206 |date=2009-02-22 }}</ref> <!--UNESCO Endangered Language Criteria: 1. Vulnerable, 2. Definitely Endangered, 3. Severely Endangered, 4. Critically Endangered, 5. Extinct-->
== History == Khinalug is the language of the village Khinalug in the Quba district of Azerbaijan. It has been tentatively classified by previous researchers as a member of the Lezgian family of the Dagestani branch of Northeast Caucasian languages<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Clifton|first=J.M.|date=2005|title=The sociolinguistic situation of the Khinalug in Azerbaijan|url=http://www-01.sil.org/silesr/2005/silesr2005-007.pdf|journal=|doi=|pmid=|access-date=}}</ref> Although Khinalug is the official language of the village, it is mostly spoken by villagers in informal circumstances, while the national language [[Azerbaijani language|Azerbaijani]] is used formally for educational purposes and to communicate with non-Khinalug speakers.<ref name=":0" /> Khinalug is considered to be a [[Endangered Language|threatened]] language. This is in part due to the breaking down of a road that leads into the village, leaving it mostly isolated.<ref name=":7">{{Cite journal|last=Schulze|first=Wolfgang|date=2003|title=[Khinulag]|journal=Anthropological Linguistics|volume=450|issue=4|pages=450}}</ref>
==Vocabulary== The following words were [[Phonetic transcription|phonetically transcribed]] from Khinalug:<ref>{{cite book|last=Lubotsky|first=Alexander|title=Van Sanskriet tot Spijkerschrift: Breinbrekers uit alle talen|language=Dutch|trans-title=From Sanskrit to Cuneiform: Brain teasers from all languages|pages=12, 58–59|access-date=30 April 2016|publisher=Amsterdam University Press|year = 2010|isbn=9089641793|url=http://dare.uva.nl/cgi/arno/show.cgi?fid=174594}}</ref> {| class="wikitable" |- ! Khinalug singular !! Khinalug plural !! Translation |- | arhaz || arhazırdır || [[Pen (enclosure)|pen]] (enclosure for livestock) |- | c’imir || c’imirdir || [[sparrow]] |- | izin || izindir || [[Gums|gingiva]] |- | kırab || kırabırdır || [[galoshes]] |- | mısır || mısırdır || [[rope]] |- | nek’id || nek’idirdir || [[Human back|back]] |- | t’uk’un || t’uk’undur || [[cheek]] |- | t’umbol || t’umboldur || [[prune]] |- | ustot || ustoturdur || [[wikt:pepper|pepper]] |- | ustul || ustuldur || [[Table (furniture)|table]] |- | dalıg || dalιgιrdιr || [[work (disambiguation)|work]] |- | culoz || culozurdur || [[tooth]] |- | jalkan || jalkandιr || [[Mane (horse)|mane]] |- | kotuk || kotukurdur || [[tree stump]] |- | mekteb || mektebirdir || [[school]] (compare: [[maktab]]) |- | mizer || mizerdir || [[textile]] |}
Note: ı is roughly pronounced as the ''e'' in "fall''e''n". u is roughly pronounced as the ''ou'' in "c''ou''p".
